      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMO explicit \u003e\u003e\u003e implicit, especially when we face ambiguity like this.\ne.g. MultiErr contains err1 and err2. \nerr1 is annotated with a code\nerr2 is not and that is intentional, because the intention is to make it HTTP 500.\n\nI\u0027d expect [the code that chose to use MultiError] in a domain-specific way to also know what\u0027s the right way to resolve this (i.e. I am not entirely sure this generic piece of code would know what\u0027s the right thing to do)\n\nalso see my comment below",
